Package: ecocbo
Title: Cost-benefit optimization for ecological sampling
Version: 0.9.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Edlin", family = "Guerra-Castro", 
        role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "edlinguerra@gmail.com"),
    person(given = "Arturo", family = "Sanchez-Porras", 
        role = c("aut"), email = "sp.arturo@gmail.com", 
        comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1691-286X")))
Description: ecocbo is an R package designed to calculate the optimal
    cost-benefit for ecological sampling, based on data from simulated 
    ecological communities. The optimization follows the procedure proposed
    by Underwood (1997), through the processes of four functions. 
License: GPL (>= 3)
